## 🎬 SESSION END RITUAL

Before ending your turn:

### 1. UPDATE BEADS
**Beads = long-term memory.** Persist everything discovered during the session.

```bash
bd update <id> --status done    # For completed work
bd create "Fix validation bug in ApprovalService" --context "Found during BD-042, non-blocking"
bd sync
```

### 2. GIT WORKFLOW
```bash
git pull --rebase origin main
git push origin <feature-branch>
```
**Work is NOT complete until `git push` succeeds.**

### 3. EXPLORE CASES AGAIN (BEFORE SUGGESTING NEXT)
- **Again** look for functional or edge cases that are missing or incomplete.
- If the **next subsequent task** (in backlog order) would already cover a case, note it — don't suggest doing it now.
- For any gaps NOT covered by the next task, **present as options** for user choice:
  > "**Optional cases (your choice):**
  > - A) [e.g. Add logout link to Welcome page for consistency]
  > - B) [e.g. Document rate-limit message in 08-API-SPEC]
  > - C) None — proceed as-is.
  > Which do you prefer?"
- **Create beads** for any case the user chooses to defer (don't rely on memory):
  ```bash
  bd create "Add logout link to Welcome page" --type=task --body="Nice-to-have, found during BD-005."
  ```

